HEADWORD: Anagogical
<hw>An`a*gog"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Mystical; having a secondary
spiritual meaning; <as>as, the <ex>rest</ex> of the Sabbath, in an
<ex>anagogical</ex> sense, signifies the repose of the saints in heaven;
an <ex>anagogical</ex> explication.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>An`a*gog"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anagogics</ent>⟦br⟧
